"1327","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"1328","The Board of Trustees and Shareholders"
"1329","Putnam Funds Trust"
"1330","In planning and performing our audit of the financial"
"1331","statements of Putnam Dynamic Risk Allocation Fund ( the"
"1332","Fund ), as of and for the year ended May 31, 2018, in"
"1333","accordance with the standards of the Public Company"
"1334","Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered"
"1335","the Funds internal control over financial reporting,"
"1336","including controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis"
"1337","for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose of"
"1338","expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to"
"1339","comply with the requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the"
"1340","purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of"
"1341","the Funds internal control over financial reporting."
"1342","Accordingly, we express no such opinion."
"1343","Management of the Fund is responsible for establishing and"
"1344","maintaining effective internal control over financial"
"1345","reporting.  In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates"
"1346","and judgments by management are required to assess the"
"1347","expected benefits and related costs of controls.  A"
"1348","companys internal control over financial reporting is a"
"1349","process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"1350","the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation"
"1351","of financial statements for external purposes in accordance"
"1352","with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP).  A"
"1353","companys internal control over financial reporting includes"
"1354","those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the"
"1355","maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail,"
"1356","accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and"
"1357","dispositions of the assets of the company; (2) provide"
"1358","reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as"
"1359","necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"1360","accordance with GAAP, and that receipts and expenditures of"
"1361","the company are being made only in accordance with"
"1362","authorizations of management and trustees of the company;"
"1363","and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention"
"1364","or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or"
"1365","disposition of the companys assets that could have a"
"1366","material effect on the financial statements."
"1367","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over"
"1368","financial reporting may not prevent or detect"
"1369","misstatements.  Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"1370","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk"
"1371","that controls may become inadequate because of changes in"
"1372","conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the"
"1373","policies or procedures may deteriorate."
"1374","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting"
"1375","exists when the design or operation of a control does not"
"1376","allow management or employees, in the normal course of"
"1377","performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect"
"1378","misstatements on a timely basis.  A material weakness is a"
"1379","deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies, in internal"
"1380","control over financial reporting, such that there is a"
"1381","reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of a"
"1382","funds annual or interim financial statements will not be"
"1383","prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"1384","Our consideration of the Funds internal control over"
"1385","financial reporting was for the limited purpose described"
"1386","in the first paragraph and would not necessarily disclose"
"1387","all deficiencies in internal control that might be material"
"1388","weaknesses under standards established by the Public"
"1389","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States)."
"1390","However, we noted the following matter involving internal"
"1391","control over financial reporting and its operation that we"
"1392","consider to be a material weakness as defined above."
"1393","These conditions were considered in determining the nature,"
"1394","timing, and extent of the procedures to be performed in our"
"1395","audit of the financial statements of the Fund for the year"
"1396","ended May 31, 2018, and this report does not affect our"
"1397","report thereon dated July 17, 2018."
"1398","The Fund did not have appropriate financial reporting"
"1399","controls to identify the mispricing of a commodity linked"
"1400","note due to an incorrect security setup by the Funds"
"1401","pricing vendor. As a result of this material weakness,"
"1402","there was a material misstatement in the preliminary May"
"1403","31, 2018 financial statements that was corrected prior to"
"1404","issuance.  The material weakness was considered in"
"1405","determining the nature, timing, and extent of audit tests"
"1406","applied in our audit of the financial statements of the"
"1407","Fund for the year ended May 31, 2018, and this report does"
"1408","not affect our report thereon dated July 17, 2018."
"1409","This report is intended solely for the information and use"
"1410","of management and the Board of Trustees of Putnam Funds"
"1411","Trust and the Securities and Exchange Commission and is not"
"1412","intended to be and should not be used by anyone other than"
"1413","these specified parties."
